section.heading: Fictitious name indictments for first or second degree sexual abuse or first or second degree child sexual abuse.

annotations.annotation: Section 4 of D.C. Law 15-356 provided as follows: “Sec. 4. Applicability. This act shall apply to an offense committed before its effective date only if the statute of limitations for the offense has not expired prior to the effective date.”
D.C. Law 16-191 made a technical change in the language of D.C. Law 15-356 that resulted in no change in text.
Section 5(c) of D.C. Law 22-311 provided that the repeal of this section by D.C. Law 22-311 shall not affect prosecutions commenced before May 3, 2019.
